messages.text: How’s the dig today?
We uncovered one of the most baffling pieces I’ve seen.
Haven’t seen any artifacts, Mayan or otherwise, that looks like this thing.
Really?? What is it?
Looks like a pair of ancient goggles or something similar. But get this, the insides are lined with crystal.
Hm. What kind?
Well that’s actually the crazy part. Nobody has ever seen this kind of crystal. It’s completely unknown to modern science.
What the hell… what’s it look like?
You’re not going to believe this…
What??
It’s translucent and lavender-pink. But Tim the insides of it seem to be um...alive?
Alive??
Yeah, there appear to be darker pink clouds within the crystal that move around sort of. They respond to movement and sound.
I have to see this.
Yeah you’ll be seeing it. In text books.
Congrats my love!
Thanks. Gotta go for now. Final stretch before break.
later that night
You back at base camp?
Yeah.
How’d everything go?
Good. Finished excavating the goggles with no damage.
You pack them up and send to the lab?
They’re actually here in my room. Wanted to examine them personally first.
So what do they look like? Besides the crystal.
They’re stone. Sort of the shape of ski goggles...
...with what looks like a head strap made of a brilliantly preserved fibrous plant.
At first I thought the goggles may be for eye protection during battle, but you can’t actually see past the crystal.
It’s too thick.
Interesting.
I think they might be a wearable looking glass of some kind.
Did you try them on?
The oils on my skin could cause deterioration.
How can you assess their purpose without trying them out?
Suppose that’s a valid point.
Point for - TIM :)
Haha! I’ll think about it. Going to go to sleep. Long day ahead.
early the next morning
Are you up???
Thought you went to sleep?
Insomnia. Kept thinking about the goggles.  So…. I tried them on.
Oh really?
And Tim….when I did….something happened.
Did they break?
No.
What then?
A hallucination of some sort.
Were you half asleep or something? Maybe you were dreaming?
I was perfectly awake. It startled me so I took the goggles off. And when I did, the hallucination went away.
What the hell. What did you see??
I’m not really sure. My head is spinning. I don’t feel that well.
Get some rest. You’ll think more clearly.
an hour later
You still up?
Yeah. Feeling better?
Still couldn’t sleep so tried the goggles on again.  I left them on for longer.
And??
I hallucinated longer.
Only I’m not sure ‘hallucination’ is the right word. It’s more like these things were actually happening.
Jesus. What did you hallucinate?
Hard to describe. I was somewhere else entirely. Somewhere unclassifiable. Beyond description and imagination.
I believe it has something to do with the crystal.
Yeah. Probably.
But listen. While I was inhabiting wherever it is that these goggles brought me, I encountered, for a very brief second...
...what I can only describe as a deity. A god.
Are you kidding me? A GOD?
I only use these words for lack of better terminology. Whatever I encountered was not of this Earth.
Not of this reality, and certainly not something capable of being imagined by a human mind. Something utterly alien.
I can’t believe this.
I think these goggles were used by the Maya to communicate with this being. And perhaps other beings.
They are meant to show us a reality beyond our own.
Do you think these beings are the foundation of Mayan mythology? We have to figure out what this crystal is...
Maybe. Did some research after and whatever I saw had a vague resemblance to the Mayan deity Itzamna who created all things.
The universe. Matter. Everything.
I’ll text you in a bit. I’m going to put the goggles on again.
I want to see if I can possibly see whatever this was for longer. Maybe communicate with it.
You don’t know what you’re dealing with. Just send it to the lab.
I’ll be okay.
Just be careful.
an hour later
Anything new?
Dana?
DANA
You there????
a few hours later
Dana you awake?
an hour later
Tim, this is Veronica Ullman I work with Dana.
Have you seen her at all???
Are you able to speak on the phone?
Is something wrong?
I’m going to call you. I prefer to tell you over the phone.
???? What’s going on????? If something has happened just tell me here.
I don’t think I can bear to hear whatever it is over the phone.
Tim, I am so sorry. Dana is dead.
Tim, are you still there?
Yes. I’m here.
What happened?
Please tell me.
Yes. We found her in her room wearing an artifact that we’d uncovered the previous day. It was strapped to her head.
Oh god.
Her face was contorted into an expression of pure horror.
Jesus.
I’m sorry.
Please make sure nobody else puts on those goggles.
Do you know anything about what happened to her? Was she in communication with you?
I believe I know what happened. I believe that Dana’s mind was exposed to something it simply could not comprehend.
I believe she probably went insane and died of shock.
What did she tell you?
Veronica, you are not going to believe this...
